# Axodus Portfolio Request Queue

Last updated: 2026-06-04

Baseline: RECAST 01 and PORTFOLIO SPRINT 01 allocation.

This queue is ordered for portfolio balance. It is not approval to implement runtime, execution, production config, credentials, trading, swaps, settlement, treasury, payouts, wallet signing, or on-chain writes.

## REQ-01: Global Docs / Instructions Recovery - L1 to L2

- Objective: decide how global `.instructions` are versioned, owned, and validated.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: versioning options, ownership map, source-of-truth map, validation checklist, non-destructive docs updates.
- Forbidden actions: initialize/move root repo, delete reports, destructive restructuring, production claims.
- Expected deliverables: versioning decision memo, owner map, L2 exit checklist, validation command list.
- Validation: required-file checks and root `git status --short --branch || true`.
- Maturity exit criteria: global docs have a documented versioning/ownership strategy and repeatable validation checklist.

## REQ-02: Documentation Nucleus Recovery - L3 to L4

- Objective: recover Documentation nucleus instruction structure.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Documentation/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: create/update STATUS, ROADMAP, WORKFLOW, SECURITY, and docs validation criteria.
- Forbidden actions: publish official release docs, overwrite strategy, change product/runtime behavior.
- Expected deliverables: nucleus status/workflow/security/roadmap stubs and docs readiness criteria.
- Validation: `git diff --check -- .instructions` and safe docs-file existence checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: Documentation has complete nucleus instruction structure and L4 readiness criteria.

## REQ-03: BBA-Agency Recovery - L2 to L3

- Objective: define BBA mock/local evidence and non-production validation gate.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/BBA-Agency/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: validation plan, route evidence checklist, TypeScript/Zod contract validation steps, production-claim review.
- Forbidden actions: production campaign execution, real billing, external automation execution, payment flows.
- Expected deliverables: L3 exit checklist, claim-risk register, validation plan.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file existence checks only unless a separate validation gate is approved.
- Maturity exit criteria: BBA has a documented non-production validation path to L3.

## REQ-04: Lottery Recovery - L2 to L3

- Objective: move Lottery from backlog to controlled recovery.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Lottery/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: STATUS recovery plan, compliance boundary docs, mock/read-only route validation plan, randomness/VRF design stub, prize/payout gate docs.
- Forbidden actions: prize execution, payouts, treasury movement, production VRF, contract deployment, on-chain writes.
- Expected deliverables: L3 recovery checklist, compliance blocker map, randomness/payout boundary note.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and optional read-only file checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: Lottery has mock/local L3 criteria without execution authority.

## REQ-05: Dex Visibility Planning - L3 to L4 Without Swaps

- Objective: plan DEX read-only visibility without enabling swaps or settlement.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Dex/.instructions` and approved DEX registry docs only.
- Allowed actions: route metadata documentation, registry-to-app map, token-list boundary docs, no-swap UI/contract map.
- Forbidden actions: swaps, routing execution, settlement, token-list repo mutation, linked fork mutation, treasury execution.
- Expected deliverables: DEX L4 visibility plan, no-swap/no-settlement gate, vendor-safe file list.
- Validation: documentation diff checks; no vendor/fork traversal beyond approved paths.
- Maturity exit criteria: DEX has a read-only L4 visibility plan with explicit execution-disabled boundaries.

## REQ-06: Mining Visibility Consolidation - L3 to L4

- Objective: consolidate Mining read-only visibility and provider boundary evidence.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Mining/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: AxodusAPP visibility map, provider mock/read-only API docs, non-execution flag review, payout/accounting gates.
- Forbidden actions: provider custody, accounting execution, compliance execution, treasury, payout execution, real provider execution.
- Expected deliverables: L4 visibility checklist, provider boundary map, payout/accounting blocker register.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file existence checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: Mining has L4 visibility and read-only contract criteria.

## REQ-07: Academy Contract Consolidation - L4 to L5

- Objective: consolidate Academy contracts/read models without value-bearing execution.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Academy/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: OpenAPI/read-model documentation, repository contract review, mock PoK boundary clarification, reward/credential gates.
- Forbidden actions: real credential issuance, reward execution, minting, transfers, withdrawals, financial-value semantics.
- Expected deliverables: L5 contract/read-model checklist, reward/credential blocker map.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file checks; no contract tests unless separately approved.
- Maturity exit criteria: Academy has L5 documentation-level contract/read-model readiness.

## REQ-08: Business Contract Consolidation - L4 to L5

- Objective: consolidate Business contracts, ACS bridge boundaries, and approval read models.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Business/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: ACS bridge docs, repository contract consolidation, approval-state read model docs, AxodusAPP route contract map.
- Forbidden actions: real approvals, persistence promotion, production business execution, financial commitments.
- Expected deliverables: L5 contract map, persistence blocker map, approval-state boundary note.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: Business has L5 contract/read-only approval model criteria.

## REQ-09: Defi Contract Consolidation - L4 to L5 Without Execution

- Objective: define Defi Phase 3 contract/interface readiness without implementation authority.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Defi/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: Phase 3 contract planning, adapter interface boundaries, simulated receipt docs, accounting/reconciliation design, risk constraints.
- Forbidden actions: custody, staking execution, rebalancing, validator scoring execution, fund movement, production oracle/accounting/reconciliation.
- Expected deliverables: L5 non-executing interface map, custody/governance decision dependencies, risk blocker register.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: Defi has L5 planning evidence without execution approval.

## REQ-10: Marketplace L6 Readiness Gap Analysis - No Production Payments

- Objective: identify Marketplace L6 gaps without enabling production payments or settlement.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Marketplace/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: endpoint contract completeness review, production blocker map, settlement/payment boundary docs, bridge/LayerZero gate docs.
- Forbidden actions: wallet transactions, blockchain writes, external payment gateways, treasury, production bridge messages, settlement, minting, value-bearing asset transfer, payments.
- Expected deliverables: L6 gap report, payment/settlement blocker map, endpoint contract completeness table.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: Marketplace has a bounded L6 readiness gap analysis, not production readiness.

## REQ-11: AxodusAPP Real Data Readiness Plan - No Real Execution

- Objective: plan mock-to-real read-only data readiness across modules.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/AxodusAPP/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: integration contract map, module visibility matrix, mock-to-real transition checklist, frontend boundary docs.
- Forbidden actions: real execution flows, live transaction initiation, wallet signing, production backend switching, treasury or settlement actions.
- Expected deliverables: L5 readiness plan, module matrix, backend gate dependency map.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: AxodusAPP has read-only real-data readiness criteria with execution disabled.

## REQ-12: Core L6 Backlog Control - No Execution Authority

- Objective: keep Core L6 work bounded to backlog criteria and certification maps.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Core/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: L6 backlog definition, consumer certification map, public API stability criteria, registry ownership docs, versioning policy.
- Forbidden actions: execution authority, treasury controls, product decisions, production runtime authority.
- Expected deliverables: L6 backlog criteria, consumer certification map, registry ownership note.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: Core L6 backlog is explicit and not implementation-pulled.

## REQ-13: Governance HOLD Backlog Control - No API Executor

- Objective: maintain Governance HOLD and prevent transport/executor drift.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Governance/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: API transport gap docs, executor gate docs, read-only contract/interface inventory, validation maintenance notes.
- Forbidden actions: API transport implementation, HTTP controllers/routes, real DB, AxodusAPP real client, executor, treasury, on-chain writes.
- Expected deliverables: HOLD backlog update, no-executor gate, read-only interface inventory.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: Governance HOLD is current and execution/API expansion is still blocked.

## REQ-14: ACS HOLD Backlog Control - No Runtime Mutation

- Objective: keep ACS as a controlled dependency without runtime mutation.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/ACS/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: backlog control, contract docs, readiness gap list, risk docs.
- Forbidden actions: runtime mutation, Hummingbot control, trading, treasury movement, credential access, Governance/Core bypass.
- Expected deliverables: ACS HOLD note, dependency map, runtime mutation blocker register.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file checks.
- Maturity exit criteria: ACS HOLD is current and runtime mutation remains blocked.

## REQ-15: Trading HOLD Backlog Control - No Live Trading

- Objective: keep Trading in HOLD while planning credential and vendor ownership safely.
- Scope: `/opt/Axodus/Trading/.instructions`.
- Allowed actions: credential vault planning, paper/local boundary docs, live-trading blocker register, vendor ownership plan.
- Forbidden actions: live trading, real exchange keys, withdrawals, production Credential Vault/KMS/HSM, production DB, treasury actions, vendor ownership changes.
- Expected deliverables: Trading HOLD update, Credential Vault decision backlog, live-trading blocker register.
- Validation: documentation diff checks and safe file checks; no `trading:local:e2e` unless separately approved.
- Maturity exit criteria: Trading HOLD is current and live/credential execution remains disabled.

## Queue Policy

- Execute REQ-01 before broad root documentation expansion.
- Execute recovery requests before L5/HOLD requests unless a blocker requires immediate control.
- Every request must restate production-disabled boundaries and must include its own validation/report artifact.
